	(203,1,'2015-03-08 13:25:38','2015-03-08 13:25:38','My inaugural Abbot + Water blog topic is something I like to practice as much as I preach: creating moments of calm in the storm that is everyday life to feed your soul and creativity. About two years ago, I had the good fortune of working with Natasha Uspensky, a nutritionist who was secretly really good at life coaching. She helped me rehab from a place of no, I cant - Im busy and have no time for anything because Im working mom and you just dont understand that I HAVE NO TIME to a place of yes, I can. I will add that this was a gradual transition from no to yes, but being open to the idea is a great starting point!\r\n<!--more-->\r\nIve written about this before, because it is so powerful. Finding time for calm  be it meditation, exercise, journaling, cooking, or whatever you need to turn off your brain  is critical. I understand the place of no; as a working single mom with hobbies, an overly active social life and a passion for doing stuff with my son, it pretty easy to see a crushed schedule with competing priorities. But I promise you, finding calm in your storm, even 15 minutes per day, will help.\r\n\r\nMy calm of choice is guided meditation. For those (like me) who are novices, try Oprah and Deepaks 21-Day Meditation Challenges. Every quarter, this power duo releases a FREE challenge, which they narrate. The topics range, Ive found the content to be terrific overall. Their next challenge just happens to begin on Monday, March 16th  and you can sign up here. You can also check out two cool apps  Meditation Timer and Calm  great for on-the-go or when traveling.\r\n\r\nMy other calm of choice is being lazy when life allows. On the cusp of a trip to Austin, Texas for SXSW, I had the opportunity to be very lazy, getting my calm on at my friends house in Connecticut. While we didnt meditate, per se, we did sit fireside, wine and cheese at the ready, for about two days. So, if you cant meditate, try to recreate our Saturday (shown above)!\r\n\r\nxx\r\n\r\nHeather','Creating Calm in the Storm','','publish','open','open','','creating-calm-in-the-storm','','','2015-03-12 21:13:36','2015-03-12 21:13:36','',0,'http://abbot-water.dev/?p=203',1,'post','',0),
